track_notes: This path is not allowed when ski resort is open unless you use ski. The landscape is very nice, and if the sky is clear you can see Corsica Island

Not the longest but surely the harest way to this summit. You can park in the village and there is a lot of room for antenna on summit; the view is wonderfull to the Mercantour chain and South you can see the sea with lsland Lérins and also Corsica Island. If you clim in winter, you may need some snowshoes and in summer take enought water for the journey.
This track shows the way down/up that you can use! the sloope is 30 degres!!! only 2km
As the ski resort does not allow walker every where, you must use alternative path! this one is fine.
Park at Coursegoules, then follow the long crest. plenty room for antenna. nice panorama
yet another path; in winter with snowshoes the path is different, in summer it could be hot!
Found this way down very short and easy
